WEBVTT

NOTE Skit begins at anchor #7.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
[caption] Film leader: 9…8…7…6…31…6…Jimmy Greaves…4…3…

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:10.000
[action] Victorian-texture film: Queen Victoria and Gladstone walk on lawn at Osborne.

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:20.000
<v Voice Over (John Cleese)>
These historic pictures of Queen Victoria… commentary recorded on earliest wax cylinders… spoken by Alfred Lord Tennyson, the Poet Laureate.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:40.000
<v Commentary (Michael Palin)>
Well hello, it's the wacky Queen again! And who's the other fella? It's Willie Gladstone! [action] Queen nudges and chucks Gladstone; hosepipe antics; gardener kicked; Gladstone sprayed.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:55.000
[action] Queen runs; later paints fence; daubs Gladstone; he pours bucket on her; she kicks him; he falls through fence.

00:00:55.000 --> 00:01:02.000
[action] Tea on lawn; Queen pies Gladstone; freeze-frame; pull back to photo on mantel in a working-class sitting room.

